Reasoning: The paper discusses a new theory for modeling dynamical systems using predictive state representations (PSRs) and observable operator models (OOMs). This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), robotics (cs.RO), and information theory (cs.IT). Given the focus on modeling and prediction, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY and cs.RO for their relevance to control and robotics applications. The discussion of the systemdynamics matrix and its relationship to other models may also make cs.IT a relevant category.
